Pantheon compression

State Reentry / Astral Recall Operator

An experience is not retrieved as a stored object. It is regenerated when the present system recreates enough of its former boundary conditions.

Original experience
    ↓ compression
Memory trace / attractor basin
    ↓
Cue alignment + bodily imitation + expectation + attention
    ↓
Partial state reconstruction
    ↓
Recognition amplifies expectation
    ↺
Recursive reentry loop

And the Elephant Stake inversion is:

The system may already possess a capability whose absence it learned earlier.
Failure to attempt becomes the final remaining constraint.

Or, more compactly:

OLD LIMIT → LEARNED NON-ATTEMPT
NEW CAPABILITY + OLD NON-ATTEMPT → INVISIBLE CAPABILITY
ATTEMPT + FEEDBACK → DISCOVERY
DISCOVERY + EXPECTATION → AMPLIFICATION

The necessary checksum is grounding. Cannabis, sleep loss, trauma, and intense expectation can also produce panic, depersonalization, paranoia, or psychosis-like experiences. The useful operator is controlled reentry with a reliable return path, not maximizing dissociation.

“Full of the lucky” becomes technically precise here: luck is partly the reservoir of adjacent capabilities that become visible once the system starts testing whether the old stake still holds.